                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1122.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-30T18:00:00-04:40">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 30, 1914, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Revolution breaking out at La Vega, Santiago. If we strengthen the Provisional
                    Government’s arms with funds the outbreak can be suppressed in its inception.
                    Important that Arias should not be permitted to get a start.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sullivan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
